<Base title="About — Hankyeol Kyung">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I'm an agent engineer focused on making AI systems that work in practice --
    not demos, but tools people rely on. The interesting problems right now are
    about memory, autonomy, and how agents fit into real workflows.
  </p>

  <p>
    At <a href="https://asleep.ai">Asleep</a>, I build sleep analysis products,
    voice agents, and the infrastructure connecting them. Outside of work, I build
    personal systems that treat agents as collaborators -- external memory,
    knowledge retrieval, ambient interfaces.
  </p>

  <h2>Beliefs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Ship over polish. Real users over toy demos.</li>
    <li>Good infrastructure disappears.</li>
    <li>The best agent systems are collaborative, not theatrical.</li>
    <li>Agents should extend how you think, not replace it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Interests</h2>
  <p>
    Agents as teammates. External memory and personal knowledge systems.
    The gap between agent demos and agent products.
    AI-native workflows that respect the human in the loop.
  </p>
</Base>
